# SSO + SCIM demo PR #1

This PR introduces a small, demo-friendly foundation for **SAML SSO configuration** and **SCIM provisioning** work.

## What’s in scope (for the demo)
- A basic “tenant/workspace” **SSO configuration object**
- Validation for common IdP inputs:
  - **IdP Entity ID**
  - **SSO URL**
  - **X.509 signing certificate**
- A placeholder path for parsing **IdP metadata XML**
- A few simple tests to show expected behaviour

## Why this exists
Enterprise customers typically want:
- **SSO (SAML)** for centralised authentication
- **SCIM** for automated provisioning and deprovisioning (access hygiene)

This PR focuses on the configuration and guardrails needed before implementing the full auth + provisioning flows.

## Example config (illustrative)
```

{

"idpEntityId": "https://idp.example.com/metadata",

"ssoUrl": "https://idp.example.com/saml2/sso",

"x509Cert": "-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----nMIIC...snip...n-----END CERTIFICATE-----"

}
